nts1.d: NTS's own Giulia Tess pulls us leftfield once a month.
Bassline, 4x4, speed garage, niche… Whatever you wanna call it, Bradford veteran TS7 is bringing the Northern dance sound to a whole new generation.
Fraternal party starters The Twins takeover for regular trips into electroclash, experimental electronics, and Desi sounds, inviting on boundary pushing collaborators and friends.

Croatian DIY label Low Income $quad showcase their catalogue and extended family of producers - Expect neo trance sounds, reworked Memphis rap acapellas, 90s-inspired fast techno and noisy experimentalism.
Traversing East and South East Asian contemporary music with Ho Chi Minh City crew Rắn Cạp Đuôi.

Often working on rudimentary and opaquely designed "chiptune" hardware, and asked to use pseudonyms to avoid the approaches of rival video game companies, the women of Capcom's seminal Sound Team composed a multitude of now iconic video game standards. 
This one hour special covers everything from Manami Matsumae and Tamayo Kawamoto's work on early SNES classics such as Mega Man & No Way Home to Akari Kaida & Sayaka Fujita's contributions to the groundbreaking survival horror of Resident Evil & Dino Crisis
Visual artist and founder and editor-in-chief of The Editorial Magazine Claire Milbrath joins us for an hour of ambient, classical, and italian library music.
Los Angeles native & synth pioneer Benedek blends ambient, boogie, funk & more, once a month from our LA studio.

nts1.n: THE EARLY BIRD SHOW W/ PAM
nts1.d: PAM, previously host of beloved NTS show Okonkole Y Trompa, joins you for a dawn chorus every Thursday. Traversing obscure rarities, globetrotting vintage pop and beyond.

nts1.n: THE NTS BREAKFAST SHOW W/ FLO
nts1.d: Breakfast, in Flo motion - served by Flo Dill, every Monday to Thursday.
Low, slow and sleazy sounds with babyschön, in the studio for the early afternoon shift…
Musical peregrinations from Gabi, guiding listeners through new wave, post punk and synth.

Longtime NTS resident, producer, vocalist and DJ Fauzia guides us through the multiplicity of her influences and tastes for an hour each month. Expect everything from frenetic club productions to classical composition, experimental electronics and beyond.

nts1.n: SECRET SUNDAZE: 'Flashlight' / Blues Dance special w/ Ed Gillett & David Llewellyn
nts1.d: London based DJ, producer, curator, band-leader and 9FINITY label boss Secretsundaze live from the studio for a bi-monthly exploration of carefully filtered house music through the lens of the rave continuum.

nts1.n: NTS Guide to: Rare Groove Inspired Jungle
nts1.d:
Jungle would not exist without samples, and sampling culture. The foundational bedrock of the genre – the break – are isolated drum sections from older records, most notably the break from The Winstons' "Amen Brother". This re-imagining of classic soul, jazz and R&B music often extends to the melodic samples in jungle, creating a distinctive softer side to the genre, recalling slow jams and emotive ballads. 
Tim Reaper selects two hours of tough but emotional rare groove-inspired Jungle records.

nts1.n: THE EXHIBITION HOUR W/ DAZEGXD & CHEETAH (R)
nts1.d: This month's episode features renowned junglist producer & DJ Cheetah from London.

nts1.n: GHOST NOTES WORLDWIDE w/ Impey & Nicky Soft Touch
nts1.d: Tune into Ghost Notes Worldwide for that post-twilight sound. Night time music of all strains, with blunted R&B and hip hop instrumentals, neo-downtempo productions, slow jams, and hazy dancefloor sounds.

nts1.n: drizle.FM w/ PLO MAN & DJ Trystero
nts1.d: forwards and backwards through bits of a [mostly] electronic music timeline. reverence for BCR. records i’ve played forever and new records i’ve just found. boil it down. one z in drizle.

CHANNELING W/ IVAN SMAGGHE & NATHAN GREGORY WILKINS (R)

THE NTS BREAKFAST SHOW w/ FINN
SOUP TO NUTS W/ SCARY THINGS

KUTMAH PRESENTS: The Last Sketchbook w/ ALIA

nts2.n: THE WINDMILLS OF YOUR MIND w/ Taylor Rowley
nts2.d:
DJ & music supervisor Taylor Rowley forages for the forgotten musical past every month, uncovering soundtracks, psych rock & other treasures.
From the host: "Thanks for tuning in this year. Happy holidays

nts2.n: SOLID STATE SURVIVOR W/ SHAGS CHAMBERLAIN (R)
nts2.d: Broadcasting from LA, Shags dives deep into his wild array of records, bringing a strong thematic focus each month.
Modern melancholia, waves from yesterdays, teenage rebellion and electronic electronics.
The inimitable Kranky Ltd, live from LA once a month.

Past, present and future soundtracks from Beirut to Bangkok via Bombay.
From the host: "Nin aan dhul marini dhaayo maleh."
Tokyo-based DJ & composer Abiu taking you to a higher state, playing tracks from across the house axis.

nts2.n: THE HEAD ZONE W/ RIPLEY JOHNSON
nts2.d: Step into The Head Zone - one hour of musical selections from the mind of Moon Duo's Ripley Johnson.
NahhG hosts Tuesday Trips, exploring the different sounds of underground beats and hip-hop alongside special guest mixes from current beatmakers and curators. - Live once a month

nts2.n: NO ID RADIO W/ ANYSIA KYM (R)
nts2.d: NYC-based producer, songwriter, and multi-instrumentalist Anysia Kym shares a monthly compilation of her favourite tracks, right now and of all time; she flips a song of her choice at the start of each hour-long episode.
New explorations in sounds from one of the most esteemed selectors in Europe, Lena Willikens.
Life on wide mode.

nts2.n: Maiba Taya!: Vintage Filipino Songs and the Echoes of Folk Memory
nts2.d: Our friends in Manila Maiba Taya! Take us on a nostalgic journey through the romance, rhythm and ritual of Filipino musical heritage, with an hour of vintage Pinoy folk songs, and Tagalog love ballads
Melbourne based producer YL HOOI share an hour of dub, electronics, postpunk and more every month…

nts2.n: WOMEN OF REGGAE W/ ESTELLE BIRCH (R)
nts2.d:
A one-off special on International Women’s Day celebrating some of the most gifted women in reggae.
Compiled & mixed by Estelle Birch.

nts2.n: Starmirror w/ Holly Herndon & Mat Dryhurst
nts2.d: An in conversation with musicians, technologists, and longtime collaborators Holly Herndon & Mat Dryhurst, featuring AI choirs and soundscapes from their new exhibition at the KW Institute for Contemporary Art in Berlin, entitled "Starmirror", on view until 18.01.26. Together, they reflect on their shared practice across machine learning, AI, and their musical influences, and present selections from the installation.

Georgia are Justin Tripp and Brian Close - and they make music, videos, films and performances from their base in Chinatown, New York. Tune in for a monthly hour of oddball electronics; whether ambient or fit for the floor…

nts2.n: AUTOTUNE THE WORLD W/ CHRISTOPHER KIRKLEY

nts2.d:
Join John Olson (aka Inzane Johnny, of Wolf Eyes) and music writer Rich Tupica as they mine deep into Michigan's wilderness of sounds. No private press rarity is off limits: soul, gospel, oddities, punk, experimental, rockabilly, and garage rock. It's all unearthed. Strap in for an insanely bizarre ride across the Great Lakes State.
From the host: "This is a mix of what Michigan has had to offer over the years. From the 1960s through today. Techno. Funk. Motown. Garage. Psych-rock. You get the point!"

A household name in her homeland of China and often considered one of East Asia's biggest pop successes, Beijing-born Faye Wong transcended the traditionally male-dominated world of Cantopop, Combining mainstream Chinese pop sounds with alternative rock and electronic music, notably covering The Cranberries and collaborating with the Cocteau Twins. A diva and an icon of alternative culture in the East, with she may be most recognisable to those in the West as the star of Wong Kar Wei's 1994 film Chungking Express. 
Listen to an hour of Faye Wong's best musical moments, compiled by Philip FM.
Fast-rising US duo Mackeeper shares half hour of selections…

Sacred Pools is a monthly show, rotating between DJ October, Faso and Toshiki Ohta. All three hosts showcase a varied and intriguing combination of music on the Sacred Pools show - from harshly metallic noise rock, unhinged post-punk, chillingly minimal synth, breakbeat rave and pervy wedding disco.
From the host: "Toshiki Ohta is a co-host on NTS’s Sacred Pools show alongside DJ October and Faso. Tosh is known for mixing between textures, genres, tempos and styles, underground and overground, with a love for pitched down jungle, pitched up breakbeat rave, EBM, dark balearic, ethereal bangers and acid rollers."

Dark Entries reissues archival and contemporary gems that prove to be crucial to our modern idea of bodily music that exists out of time. Electro, italo, cold wave, new beat, house, techno from a one-of-a-kind digger who visits dusty basements to rescue lost tapes.

DC hardcore fanatics and creators of Demystification Magazine present a regular radio session with one goal in mind: _to spread and uphold the belief and understanding that hardcore punk is an all encompassing experience that goes beyond sound and aesthetic, with an even dedication and love for the sound and aesthetic. 
From the host: "Paula runs through favorites with a few guest tracks picked by some friends."

subtle.n: Odds and Ends w/ Moon J

subtle.d: Dubversified showcases Canadian West Coast DJ talent specializing in Bass Music. Hosted by Mirage, founder of Dubversified Culture, a community-led organization focusing on music, art, and events. Mirage, originally from Québec, blends house and hip-hop since 2010, now exploring 140bpm and Deep D&B.

subtle.n: Into The Lion's Den w/ Restrikt

subtle.d: Potent Funk records’ Matt Frost - Well known for his technical abilities and Sleazy bass music style, Frost covers all angles from UK alt Rap to the LA beat scene.

Get ready to embark on a captivating sonic journey of underground music with Charlie Kelly. Including new and timeless sounds from the depths of rap, drill, grime, and experimental genres from the vibrant streets of the UK and beyond. Charlie unearths the very best in music that pushes boundaries. Off the mic, Charlie is a Radio Producer and Social Media Executive with an eclectic music taste spanning across many different cultures, decades, and styles. Hailing from North London with a love for audio and pop culture, you can expect to hear tune after tune when you’re locked into Charlie Kelly on Subtle.
BirdE brings an hour of the freshest Drum and Bass covering everything from liquid to techy steppers - the deeper the better.

Originally from Cambridge, Counter Culture's selection deftly navigates across a myriad of influences and exclusives from himself & friends.
Expect some of the freshest rolling soul straight to your headspace.

subtle.n: Strictly Business Show w/ Qua Rush & Flipz MC
5 Decades of Dub w/ Joe Vincent

subtle.d: casual_observer is a DJ and producer originally hailing from Amsterdam, where he co-organises the "moving closer" event series with friend and collaborator Bcl-2. He currently resides in Berlin. Starting his musical journey as a drummer, his music retains a heavy focus on groove, rhythm and experimentation.  Sets played by casual_observer are diverse and surprising, moving effortlessly between jungle, breaks, bass, footwork, and more. No matter the genre, his selection is sure to keep you on your toes!

In:flux Audio are a record label based in Leeds, UK founded by production duo Tik&Borrow. Since the label's inception in October 2013, they have dabbled in multiple dance music styles with the emphasis always being on the tracks being unique, and packed full of bass. Today the primary output for the label is from their Dubstep roster and this is focus of their show on Subtle - giving the artists and remixers chance to showcase their sounds with an hour guest mix, all hosted by label bossman Tik.

I’m a 19 year old DJ and producer from Newcastle upon Tyne, mainly playing and producing music around the 140bpm mark. I started out playing old 2-step and jungle records, before moving my focus to mainly dubstep and grime. Along with my friends Pirata and White Label, I run Newcastle’s only current 140 night, Well Irie.

subtle.n: THE CULTURE HEAD w. SAINT VOX

subtle.d: DIGDIS presents a selection of tracks that captures the vibrant and ever-evolving edges of dance music. Each show features a wide range of music that can be enjoyed both on the dancefloor and in more intimate listening spaces.

My show focuses on percussive, club sounds, taking inspiration from the edges of drill, funky and bass music. In both my mixes and productions, I like to keep the energy high and a little whimsical. Expect some moments of ambient and R&B too, just so we can all catch our breath.
With a monthly show on Subtle, Niceup is a London based DJ with a unique style. Pushing UKG, Breakbeat, Bass, Electro and 140. Weaving through genres showcasing new releases and older cuts.

dublab.d: “Dying Songs focuses on melancholic electronic music but isn’t limited to that. Sometimes it gets dark, sometimes I try to mix techno awkwardly, sometimes i get nostalgic… I like stuff that’s dreamy, ghostly, pretty and sad. I’ll try out new productions of my own, as well. I’m keeping it pretty open and we’ll see how it evolves.” – Jimmy
